#*: I'm '''poor as a church mouse''', but I wake up a happy man.
#* '''1932''', April 9,  Isidor Schneider, ''Hard Luck Of Poets'', The New York Times,
#*: "As poor as a poet" would be quite as comprehensible as "as '''poor as a church mouse'''."
